    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-15T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="508"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1155: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-15T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 15, 1933—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. As a consequence of attack by Peruvian planes on Colombian vessels in
                    Brazilian and Colombian waters Colombian Minister at Lima has been instructed to
                    ask for passports and Peruvian Minister here was handed his this morning at
                        11.<note n="25" xml:id="d508fn25">See section entitled “Assumption by the
                        American Embassy in Peru of Colombian Interests in Peru; Sacking of the
                        Colombian Legation”, <ref target="#pg_549">pp. 549</ref> ff.</note> Olaya
                    does not intend to declare war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
